      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The snowpack is unfavourably layered and its surface has a melt-freeze crust that is strong in many cases. As a consequence of high temperatures and solar radiation a treacherous avalanche situation will develop. These conditions will cause a weakening of the snowpack in gullies and bowls and behind abrupt changes in terrain. This applies in particular on steep south, southwest and west facing slopes above the tree line. <br/>"
      },
